
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class User {
  +id: String (unique)
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +dateOfBirth: Date
  -account: Account
}

class Account {
  +accountNumber: String (unique)
  +type: String ("personal" | "business")
  -user: User
}

class BusinessAccount {
  +companyName: String
  +monthlyFee: Double
  -- extends Account
}

class PersonalAccount {
  -- extends Account
}

class Page {
  +name: String (unique per account)
  +visitCount: Integer
  -account: Account
}

class AdvertisementPage {
  +bounceRate: Double
  +clickThroughRate: Double
  +conversionRate: Double
  -- extends Page
}

class FriendRequest {
  +fromUser: User
  +toUser: User
  +status: String ("pending" | "accepted" | "rejected")
}

' Relationships

User --> Account
Account <|-- BusinessAccount
Account <|-- PersonalAccount
Account --> Page
PersonalAccount --> Page
Page <|-- AdvertisementPage
PersonalAccount --> FriendRequest

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **User**: Represents a user who wants to join Facepage. They have personal information and are linked to exactly one `Account`.
- **Account**: An abstract class representing both types of accounts (`BusinessAccount` and `PersonalAccount`). Each account has a unique `accountNumber` and is associated with one `User`.
- **BusinessAccount**: A subclass of `Account`. It requires a company name and monthly fee.
- **PersonalAccount**: A subclass of `Account`. It can send/receive friend requests and grant privileges to other pages.
- **Page**: A page created by an account. Each page has a unique name within the account.
- **AdvertisementPage**: A subclass of `Page`, specifically for business accounts. It stores metrics like bounce rate, click-through rate, and conversion rate.
- **FriendRequest**: A request sent from one user to another. Only personal accounts can send or receive these.

